summary: Imagine Jon Snow and Robb Stark are in love with you, a closeted lesbian.
body:
Imagine Jon Snow and Robb Stark are in love with you, a closeted lesbian.

Robb’s present made it to your desk at the ministry. All wizards and witches knew Robb was the bachelor of the decade and a very honorable man, not saying the best auror and the most skillful wizard in the department against magical crimes. If you could only love him back…

Later that day, waking by the hallways, in a sudden corner you bump into Jon Snow, Robb’s half brother. Your small gift box almost fell from your arms as Jon tried to steady himself.

“Jon?”

“Y/N!” He blushed instantly. “It’s good to see you….listen I…was ykno..was thinking we uh…we could um…if you want…” Jon studdered every word out of his lips, and as every second passed without any response of you his cheeks got redder. But this feud between the Stark brothers had to stop. You had to tell him the truth.

“Jon, listen…”

He looked at the small box in your arms an saw the tag with the name of his brother. He smiled sorrowfully,“…is Robb right? I can see the way he looks at you. He is the right one. And if he is the one you choose, I promise you I will not step between you two-“

“No….it’s not that…I’m not into him…nor in any other guy.” your voice tried to point out what you had been keeping private for several years but Jon didn’t seem to get it. “What does that mean?” He frowned confused.

You tried hard not to giggle. “oh…you kow nothing.”

body:
Oathbreaker, Oathkeeper

Notice how Jon broke every single oath he’s taken but one?

He broke his vows to the Night’s Watch.

He betrayed the Wildlings.

He gave up the North to Daenerys.

He killed Daenerys, whom he claims is his queen.

Except for one. His promise to Sansa.

“I’ll protect you, I promise.”

I guess Jon has to break an oath to keep an oath.

Plus, I like how Sansa, the person Jon promises to protect, ends up protecting him.

Now, ain’t that poetic.

summary:
When Ramsay held you, it hurt. His nails would dig into your
skin. His eyes tore your costume off, and his lips would brush your...
body:
When Ramsay held you, it hurt. His nails would dig into your skin. His eyes tore your costume off, and his lips would brush your neck. He was hot to the touch, but you kept moving in his arms. As the song played, you started to dance into Jon’s arms.

Both Ramsay and Jon played your lovers in this musical. Where Ramsay’s character was a rich lord, Jon’s character was a poor hopeless romantic. Jon caught you in his arms and twirled you gently around him. His fingers were cool to the touch and he was much softer.

That is, until Jon’s eyes landed on Ramsay. When Jon held you, he gripped onto you. Ramsay’s ocean eyes drowned anything he wanted.  Jon wasn’t about to let that happen.

And now you wondered, how much of this musical was fantasy and how much of it was real-life?

That is, until Jon’s eyes landed on Ramsay. When Jon held you, he gripped onto you. Ramsay’s ocean eyes drowned anything he wanted.  Jon wasn’t about to let that happen.

And now you wondered, how much of this musical was fantasy and how much of it was real-life?

blog.name: sansasxlady
blog.title: Winter Is Coming
blog.description: Marissa, 21, lots of random content, mostly Harry Potter and Game of Thrones

summary: Sorry I can’t stop thinking about GoT.... but not really
body:
Sorry I can’t stop thinking about GoT…. but not really

I really hate how they portrayed Jon in the last season. I’m rewatching GoT because I’m in denial that it’s over and I have nothing better to do, and I’m at the part where he meets Ygritte. Now you can tell how much he loves and cares for her, yet he still stands for what he believes in, fighting for the Nights Watch, even though he knew he’d have to fight against her. I really don’t think he loved Dany as much as Ygritte and I honestly thought he’d never love again, so I was mad when they put them together to begin with. He abandons the North to bend the knee to her, knowing she would never do the same. He would never give up Winterfell like that, family has been so important to him, and all the Starks since the beginning.They really gave his character nothing in season 7 & 8, they took away all the quality’s that made him Jon Snow.
